iDN42, short for Decentralized Network 42, is a large-scale VPN		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
inetwork. Unlike traditional VPNs, DN42 utilizes technologies commonly		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ideployed on internet backbones (such as BGP), effectively simulating a		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ireal-world network environment.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iDue to its realistic nature, the barrier to entry for DN42 is		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
irelatively high. You'll need to act as an ISP (Internet Service		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iProvider): register an ASN number, obtain IPv4 and IPv6 address pools,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iand broadcast them from your server using BGP. You'll also need to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
icontact other users to establish peering connections, gradually		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iintegrating into the complete DN42 network.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iDN42 operates on the 172.20.0.0/14 and fd00::/8 address ranges – both		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ireserved for private networks. This means your activities on DN42		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iwon't interfere with your server's other internet connections.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
